# Helmsman Local Playground

## Section

Open this notebook from a local checkout of Helmsman. The setup cell installs the library from the parent directory, so reevaluating it picks up local changes.

## What You Will Do

This notebook is a guided playground for Helmsman. By the end you will:

1. Load the local checkout into Livebook.
2. Pick a ReqLLM provider and model.
3. Start a `NotebookAgent` with a system prompt and working directory.
4. Run one prompt synchronously.
5. Stream one prompt and watch events arrive live.

## How To Use It

Work from top to bottom.

* Evaluate the setup cell first.
* When a cell renders an input, pick a value in the UI before evaluating the next cell.
* If you change provider, model, API key, or system prompt, reevaluate the cells below that point.
* If you edit the local Helmsman checkout, reevaluate the setup cell to reload the dependency.

## Setup

```elixir
repo_root = Path.expand("..", __DIR__)

Mix.install([
  {:kino, "~> 0.19"},
  {:helmsman, path: repo_root}
])
```

## Catalog

This section builds a small provider catalog from ReqLLM's supported-model registry. The notebook only shows providers that expose a straightforward API key env var, because this is meant to be a simple local playground.

```elixir
defmodule HelmsmanLivebook do
  @preferred_providers ~w(anthropic openai google groq openrouter xai)

  def repo_root do
    Path.expand("..", __DIR__)
  end

  def providers do
    passing_models()
    |> Enum.group_by(& &1.provider)
    |> Enum.map(fn {provider, models} ->
      %{
        provider: provider,
        env_key: hd(models).env_key,
        model_count: length(models)
      }
    end)
    |> Enum.sort_by(fn %{provider: provider} ->
      preferred_index(provider)
    end)
  end

  def models_for(provider) do
    passing_models()
    |> Enum.filter(&(&1.provider == provider))
    |> Enum.sort_by(& &1.model)
  end

  defp passing_models do
    supported_models()
    |> Enum.filter(fn {_spec, meta} -> meta["status"] == "pass" end)
    |> Enum.map(fn {spec, meta} ->
      [provider, _model_id] = String.split(spec, ":", parts: 2)
      provider_atom = String.to_atom(provider)

      %{
        provider: provider,
        env_key: ReqLLM.Providers.get_env_key(provider_atom),
        model: spec,
        last_checked: meta["last_checked"]
      }
    end)
    |> Enum.filter(& &1.env_key)
  end

  defp supported_models do
    :req_llm
    |> :code.priv_dir()
    |> to_string()
    |> Path.join("supported_models.json")
    |> File.read!()
    |> JSON.decode!()
  end

  defp preferred_index(provider) do
    case Enum.find_index(@preferred_providers, &(&1 == provider)) do
      nil -> {1, provider}
      index -> {0, index}
    end
  end
end

providers = HelmsmanLivebook.providers()
```

```elixir
providers
|> Enum.map_join("\n", fn provider ->
  "- `#{provider.provider}`: #{provider.model_count} passing models, env key `#{provider.env_key}`"
end)
|> Kino.Markdown.new()
```

The interactive runtime form below includes the ReqLLM providers that expose a default API key env var. Providers that require a different authentication flow are intentionally left out of the picker.

## Runtime

Start by choosing a provider. After changing it, reevaluate the next cell so the model list and API key guidance match your selection.

```elixir
provider_options =
  Enum.map(providers, fn provider ->
    {provider.provider, "#{provider.provider} (#{provider.model_count} passing models, #{provider.env_key})"}
  end)

provider_input = Kino.Input.select("Provider", provider_options)
provider_input
```

```elixir
selected_provider = Kino.Input.read(provider_input)

provider_details =
  Enum.find(providers, fn provider ->
    provider.provider == selected_provider
  end)

Kino.Markdown.new("""
Selected provider: `#{selected_provider}`

ReqLLM default API key env var: `#{provider_details.env_key}`
""")
```

Now choose the concrete model and runtime settings for the session.

```elixir
models = HelmsmanLivebook.models_for(selected_provider)

model_options =
  Enum.map(models, fn model ->
    {model.model, "#{model.model} (checked #{model.last_checked})"}
  end)

model_input = Kino.Input.select("Model", model_options)
api_key_input = Kino.Input.password("API key")

system_prompt_input =
  Kino.Input.textarea(
    "System prompt",
    default: """
    You are testing Helmsman from a local Livebook.
    Be explicit about which tools you use and why.
    """
  )

cwd_input =
  Kino.Input.text(
    "Tool working directory",
    default: HelmsmanLivebook.repo_root()
  )

Kino.Layout.grid(
  [model_input, api_key_input, system_prompt_input, cwd_input],
  columns: 1
)
```

```elixir
selected_model = Kino.Input.read(model_input)

Kino.Markdown.new("""
Selected model: `#{selected_model}`

Leave the API key blank if you want ReqLLM to read `#{provider_details.env_key}` from the environment instead.
""")
```

## Agent

This defines a minimal local agent that exposes the standard coding tools. The next cell starts or restarts it with the selections you made above.

```elixir
defmodule NotebookAgent do
  use Helmsman

  @impl true
  def tools do
    Helmsman.Tools.coding_tools()
  end
end
```

```elixir
if pid = Process.whereis(NotebookAgent) do
  Process.exit(pid, :kill)
  Process.sleep(50)
end

api_key =
  api_key_input
  |> Kino.Input.read()
  |> String.trim()

start_link_opts =
  [
    name: NotebookAgent,
    model: selected_model,
    system_prompt: Kino.Input.read(system_prompt_input),
    cwd: Kino.Input.read(cwd_input)
  ] ++
    if(api_key == "", do: [], else: [api_key: api_key])

{:ok, agent} = NotebookAgent.start_link(start_link_opts)

Kino.Markdown.new("""
Started `NotebookAgent`

- model: `#{selected_model}`
- cwd: `#{Kino.Input.read(cwd_input)}`
- provider: `#{selected_provider}`
""")

agent
```

## Run

Use this section when you want the final answer only.

```elixir
prompt_input =
  Kino.Input.textarea(
    "Prompt",
    default: """
    Read README.md and summarize Helmsman's public API in 5 bullet points.
    """
  )
```

```elixir
prompt = Kino.Input.read(prompt_input)

case Helmsman.run(NotebookAgent, prompt, timeout: 120_000) do
  {:ok, response} -> Kino.Markdown.new(response)
  {:error, reason} -> Kino.Markdown.new("Run failed: `#{inspect(reason)}`")
end
```

## Stream

Use this section when you want to watch the response evolve in real time, including tool calls and tool results.

`````elixir
prompt = Kino.Input.read(prompt_input)

frame =
  Kino.Frame.new()
  |> Kino.render()

render =
  fn transcript ->
    Kino.Frame.render(frame, Kino.Markdown.new(transcript))
  end

Helmsman.stream(NotebookAgent, prompt, timeout: 120_000)
|> Enum.reduce("", fn
  {:text, chunk}, transcript ->
    updated = transcript <> chunk
    render.(updated)
    updated

  {:thinking, chunk}, transcript ->
    updated = transcript <> "\n\n> thinking: #{chunk}\n"
    render.(updated)
    updated

  {:tool_call, name, _id, args}, transcript ->
    updated =
      transcript <>
        """

        ---
        **Tool call:** `#{name}`

        ```elixir
        #{inspect(args, pretty: true, limit: :infinity)}
        ```
        """

    render.(updated)
    updated

  {:tool_result, _id, result}, transcript ->
    body =
      case result do
        value when is_binary(value) -> value
        value -> inspect(value, pretty: true, limit: :infinity)
      end

    updated =
      transcript <>
        """

        **Tool result**

        ````text
        #{body}
        ````
        """

    render.(updated)
    updated

  {:error, reason}, transcript ->
    updated = transcript <> "\n\n**Error:** `#{inspect(reason)}`\n"
    render.(updated)
    updated

  :done, transcript ->
    updated = transcript <> "\n\n---\nDone.\n"
    render.(updated)
    updated

  _event, transcript ->
    transcript
end)
`````
